00:27:04.082 --> 00:27:05.540
Although the standard
deviation has

00:27:05.540 --> 00:27:08.750
got to have the same units
as the count rate itself,

00:27:08.750 --> 00:27:10.740
because they're additive, right?

00:27:10.740 --> 00:27:13.190
Because they usually express
some count rate plus or minus

00:27:13.190 --> 00:27:15.217
either sigma or 2
sigma, so they've

00:27:15.217 --> 00:27:16.550
got to have the same count rate.

00:27:16.550 --> 00:27:19.560
So standard deviations are
expressed in counts per minute

00:27:19.560 --> 00:27:21.700
if your counts are expressed
in counts per minute.

00:27:21.700 --> 00:27:24.400
OK, cool.

00:27:24.400 --> 00:27:26.650
So we've got too many
variables, but it's

00:27:26.650 --> 00:27:29.290
easy to get rid of one of
them, either C n or C g.

00:27:29.290 --> 00:27:30.040
Do you a question?

00:27:30.040 --> 00:27:32.325
AUDIENCE: No, I was just
going to say [INAUDIBLE]..

00:27:32.325 --> 00:27:33.200
MICHAEL SHORT: Great.

00:27:33.200 --> 00:27:34.825
