00:27:36.100 --> 00:27:37.480
Cool.

00:27:37.480 --> 00:27:43.890
So we'll take out our C n, and
we'll stick in a C g minus C b.

00:27:49.320 --> 00:27:52.980
And we're trying to isolate t
g as a function of C g or vice

00:27:52.980 --> 00:27:53.970
versa.

00:27:53.970 --> 00:27:55.560
There's a lot of C
g's and not a lot

00:27:55.560 --> 00:27:59.480
of t g's, so let's just
keep the t g on its own.

00:27:59.480 --> 00:28:07.050
So we'll have 0.000625
C g minus C b squared.

00:28:07.050 --> 00:28:11.650
Then I'm going to subtract C
b over t b from both sides.

00:28:17.330 --> 00:28:25.820
Minus C b over t b
equals C g over t g.

00:28:25.820 --> 00:28:28.810
And do I have to go through the
