00:28:50.110 --> 00:28:51.760
of this expression.

00:28:51.760 --> 00:28:56.140
That number right there is
just a more exact part-- a bit

00:28:56.140 --> 00:28:57.370
of 2 Sigma.

00:28:57.370 --> 00:29:02.890
Instead of 0.05, we had
something much, much closer.

00:29:02.890 --> 00:29:06.350
So what I want us to look
at is this graph right here.

00:29:06.350 --> 00:29:09.490
We've got a nice relation
now between the count

00:29:09.490 --> 00:29:11.200
rate and counts per minute--

00:29:11.200 --> 00:29:14.440
and it was the gross count
rate and the required counting

00:29:14.440 --> 00:29:17.580
time to get to that
5% uncertainty.

00:29:17.580 --> 00:29:19.330
Well, there's a couple
