for solid angle, where

00:41:41.760 --> 00:41:44.850
the real formula
for a solid angle,

00:41:44.850 --> 00:41:47.550
you actually end up
having to do a surface

00:41:47.550 --> 00:41:53.460
integral of the sine,
which accounts for the fact

00:41:53.460 --> 00:41:55.770
that the object that you
have might be, let's say,

00:41:55.770 --> 00:41:58.310
tilted towards or away
from the detector,

00:41:58.310 --> 00:42:05.843
times some differential d phi
d theta of this unit sphere.

00:42:05.843 --> 00:42:07.260
So you'll have to
integrate to say

00:42:07.260 --> 00:42:13.740
how many of these little d
phi d thetas are actually

00:42:13.740 --> 00:42:15.840
subtended by your detector.

00:42:15.840 --> 00:42:17.940
And the value of that
actual surface integral

00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:20.430
gives you the real solid angle.

00:42:20.430 --> 00:42:22.405
That's the super
simple one if you just

00:42:22.405 --> 00:42:24.030
