OK.

01:30:46.240 --> 01:30:48.220
AUDIENCE: Should [INAUDIBLE]?

01:30:48.220 --> 01:30:50.240
FRANK WARMSLEY: Yep.

01:30:50.240 --> 01:30:59.170
So one of the things that could
change the reactor is xenon.

01:30:59.170 --> 01:31:03.250
It's a poison that builds into
the reactor while we operate.

01:31:03.250 --> 01:31:05.260
Poison in that it
absorbs neutrons

01:31:05.260 --> 01:31:06.820
not leading to fission.

01:31:06.820 --> 01:31:10.600
And it has two
ways of being made

01:31:10.600 --> 01:31:13.480
and two ways of
having it removed.

01:31:13.480 --> 01:31:18.040
One is direct from fission
and the other is decay.

01:31:18.040 --> 01:31:19.420
That's the way it's produced.

01:31:19.420 --> 01:31:25.290
The way it goes away is
basically absorbing a neutron

01:31:25.290 --> 01:31:27.550
and decaying to another isotope.

01:31:27.550 --> 01:31:31.032
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] half a
megawatt at 8.56 microamps.

01:31:31.032 --> 01:31:31.824
FRANK WARMSLEY: OK.

01:31:31.824 --> 01:31:33.260
AUDIENCE: Use the
same shim blade?

01:31:33.260 --> 01:31:36.390
FRANK WARMSLEY:
Yep, use blade 6.

01:31:36.390 --> 01:31:40.380
And what happens is when
we lower reactor power,

01:31:40.380 --> 01:31:45.240
the way we remove most of
the xenon from burn up,

01:31:45.240 --> 01:31:53.280
basically the neutrons being
absorbed by the fission

01:31:53.280 --> 01:31:54.300
process.

01:31:54.300 --> 01:32:00.300
The fact that we don't have the
reactor at a very high power

01:32:00.300 --> 01:32:02.850
means that the amount
of xenon in the core

01:32:02.850 --> 01:32:04.260
isn't being removed.

01:32:04.260 --> 01:32:06.830
So we actually start--

01:32:06.830 --> 01:32:09.510
the power would actually
want to go down on it's own.

01:32:09.510 --> 01:32:12.180
So you would have to
do a lot of re-shims.

01:32:12.180 --> 01:32:15.570
And for a while, that's a very
large amount of reactivity

01:32:15.570 --> 01:32:17.901
that has to be compensated for.

01:32:17.901 --> 01:32:19.710
For this experiment,
though, we actually

01:32:19.710 --> 01:32:22.470
shut down the reactor
yesterday and we started up

01:32:22.470 --> 01:32:23.350
early this morning.

01:32:23.350 --> 01:32:27.480
So it's not a big
factor as it normally

01:32:27.480 --> 01:32:31.055
would be after doing one of
these lowering reactor power.

01:32:31.055 --> 01:32:33.180
AUDIENCE: Do you want to
